100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 15, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva to address pressing global issues, including the ongoing tensions in the Near East. In the United States, the trial of the "Scopes Monkey" case continued, igniting debate over evolution and education. Meanwhile, in Germany, economic struggles persisted as the country grappled with hyperinflation and political instability.
